What you need to know:

Ghanaian Paul Acquah and Ugandan Mansoor Agu are the players at the centre of the ban, which was communicated to Wazito and FKF on MondayFifa's Dispute Resolution Chamber had in October 2020 ordered Wazito to pay five players it sacked over Sh6 millionAccording to lawyer Felix Majani who represented the five players in the suit, only Acquah and Agu have not received their compensation, thus the ban on the club